keywords_zh: 电导率,电流,电阻,电导量
description_zh: 西门子是电导率的单位，表示单位长度和单位面积内的电流通量的比率。西门子的倒数是欧姆。该单位被广泛用于描述电路中电容器和电导体的特性。
description_en: (Siemens) is the SI unit of electric conductance, susceptance, and admittance. The most important property of a conductor is the amount of current it will carry when a voltage is applied. Current flow is opposed by resistance in all circuits, and by also by reactance and impedance in alternating current circuits. Conductance, susceptance, and admittance are the inverses of resistance, reactance, and impedance, respectively. To measure these properties, the siemens is the reciprocal of the ohm. In other words, the conductance, susceptance, or admittance, in siemens, is simply 1 divided by the resistance, reactance or impedance, respectively, in ohms. The unit is named for the German electrical engineer Werner von Siemens (1816-1892). (  text{Siemens}equivfrac{text{A}}{text{V}}equivfrac{text{amp}}{text{volt}}equivfrac{text{F}}{text {s}}equivfrac{text{farad}}{text{second}})"

description_zh: 样本每秒是数字信号处理中描述模拟信号采样率的单位，即一秒钟内采集的样本数。赫兹也是单位制中用于测量频率的单位，即每秒钟周期数的数量。常用于描述音频和视频数据的采样率。
description_en: The number of discrete samples of some thing per second.

description_zh: 秒是时间的基本单位之一，被定义为铯原子的完整周期辐射所需的时间。它在物理、工程和科学实验中被广泛使用。
description_en:
""The (Second) (symbol: (s)) is the base unit of time in the International System of Units (SI) and is also a unit of time in other systems of measurement. Between the years1000 (when al-Biruni used seconds) and 1960 the second was defined as (1/86400) of a mean solar day (that definition still applies in some astronomical and legal contexts). Between 1960 and 1967, it was defined in terms of the period of the Earths orbit around the Sun in 1900, but it is now defined more precisely in atomic terms.

Under the International System of Units (via the International Committee for Weights and Measures, or CIPM), since 1967 the second has been defined as the duration of ({9192631770}) periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the ground state of the caesium 133 atom.In 1997 CIPM added that the periods would be defined for a caesium atom at rest, and approaching the theoretical temperature of absolute zero, and in 1999, it included corrections from ambient radiation."""

description_zh: 它是一个物理单位，用于测量能量通量密度，表示在一个平方英尺面积上的每秒能量通量。常用于照明工程中。
description_en: "Second Square Foot" is an Imperial unit for  Area Time expressed as (s-ft^{2})."

description_zh: 秒每米是衡量时间和距离之间关系的单位，表示光或声波在1米的距离内传播所需的时间。它的常见别名是米秒。
平方秒是一个物理单位，通常用于描述动量或角动量的变化速率。它表示在单位时间内，一个物体的动量或角动量所改变的面积大小。因为这个单位很少使用，所以没有常见的别名。
description_en: "Square Second" is a unit for  Square Time expressed as (s^{2})."

description_zh: 谢克是描述震荡或振动的单位，通常用于地震学和地质学中。在音频行业中，谢克也用于描述声音的强度和震荡程度。
description_en: A shake is an informal unit of time equal to 10 nanoseconds. It has applications in nuclear physics, helping to conveniently express the timing of various events in a nuclear explosion. The typical time required for one step in the chain reaction (i.e. the typical time for each neutron to cause a fission event which releases more neutrons) is of order 1 shake, and the chain reaction is typically complete by 50 to 100 shakes.
The "Shannon" is a unit of information.
The "Shannon per Second" is a unit of information rate.

description_zh: 斯勒格是一个质量单位，主要用于工程和物理学中，指的是一种非常重的质量单位，相当于32.174英尺/秒平方的力所需的质量。常用于描述物体的惯性和重量。
description_en: The slug is a unit of mass associated with Imperial units. It is a mass that accelerates by (1 ft/s) when a force of one pound-force  is exerted on it. With standard gravity (gc = 9.80665 m/s), the international foot of (0.3048 m) and the avoirdupois pound of (0.45359237 kg), one slug therefore has a mass of approximately (32.17405 lbm) or (14.593903 kg). At the surface of the Earth, an object with a mass of 1 slug exerts a force of about (32.17 lbF) or (143 N)."
"Slug per Foot" is an Imperial unit for  Mass Per Length expressed as (slug/ft)."
(Slug per Foot Second is a unit for  Dynamic Viscosity expressed as (slug/(ft-s))."
"Slug per Square Foot" is an Imperial unit for  Mass Per Area expressed as (slug/ft^{2})."
"Slug per Cubic Foot" is an Imperial unit for  Density expressed as (slug/ft^{3})."

description_zh: 它是质量流量单位，表示每秒通过某一区域的质量。常用于流体力学和传热学中描述液体或气体的流量。
description_en: "Slug per Second" is an Imperial unit for  Mass Per Time expressed as (slug/s)."

description_zh: ['DerivedUnit', 'Unit']
description_en: The steradian (symbol: sr) is the SI unit of solid angle. It is used to describe two-dimensional angular spans in three-dimensional space, analogous to the way in which the radian describes angles in a plane. The radian and steradian are special names for the number one that may be used to convey information about the quantity concerned. In practice the symbols rad and sr are used where appropriate, but the symbol for the derived unit one is generally omitted in specifying the values of dimensionless quantities.

description_zh: 它是衡量流体粘度的单位，特别适用于液体。它被广泛用于流体力学和化学工程中，用于描述流体的流动性质和阻力。
description_en: (Stokes (St)) is a unit in the category of Kinematic viscosity. This unit is commonly used in the cgs unit system. Stokes (St) has a dimension of (L^2T^{-1}) where (L) is length, and (T) is time. It can be converted to the corresponding standard SI unit (m^2/s) by multiplying its value by a factor of 0.0001."

description_zh: 史德是光通量密度单位，用于测量光源的强度。常用于照明设计和光学研究中。
description_en: (The stilb (sb) is the CGS unit of luminance for objects that are not self-luminous. It is equal to one candela per square centimeter or 10 nits (candelas per square meter). The name was coined by the French physicist A. Blondel around 1920. It comes from the Greek word stilbein meaning to glitter. It was in common use in Europe up to World War I. In North America self-explanatory terms such as candle per square inch and candle per square meter were more common. The unit has since largely been replaced by the SI unit: candela per square meter.)"

The stere is a unit of volume in the original metric system equal to one cubic metre.  The stere is typically used for measuring large quantities of firewood or other cut wood, while the cubic meter is used for uncut wood. It is not part of the modern metric system (SI). In Dutch theres also a kuub, short for kubieke meter which is similar but different.

description_en: Although the sievert has the same dimensions as the gray (i.e. joules per kilogram), it measures a different quantity. To avoid any risk of confusion between the absorbed dose and the equivalent dose, the corresponding special units, namely the gray instead of the joule per kilogram for absorbed dose and the sievert instead of the joule per kilogram for the dose equivalent, should be used.

The CGS electromagnetic unit of conductance; one absiemen is the conductance at which a potential of one abvolt forces a current of one abampere; equal to (10^{9}) siemens. One siemen is the conductance at which a potential of one volt forces a current of one ampere and named for Karl Wilhem Siemens."

description_en: The astronomical unit of mass is the solar mass.The symbol (S) is often used in astronomy to refer to this unit, although (M_{odot}) is also common. The solar mass, (1.98892 time 1030 kg), is a standard way to express mass in astronomy, used to describe the masses of other stars and galaxies. It is equal to the mass of the Sun, about 333,000 times the mass of the Earth or 1,048 times the mass of Jupiter. In practice, the masses of celestial bodies appear in the dynamics of the solar system only through the products GM, where G is the constant of gravitation."

description_zh: 特斯拉是国际单位制中用于测量磁场强度的单位，定义为在一点上产生1牛的力，对于电流强度为1安培的导线在其长度方向上受到1米的长度单位的磁场强度。常被用于描述磁场的强度、磁通量等物理量的大小。
description_en: The SI unit of flux density (or field intensity) for magnetic fields (also called the magnetic induction). The intensity of a magnetic field can be measured by placing a current-carrying conductor in the field. The magnetic field exerts a force on the conductor, a force which depends on the amount of the current and on the length of the conductor. One tesla is defined as the field intensity generating one newton of force per ampere of current per meter of conductor. Equivalently, one tesla represents a magnetic flux density of one weber per square meter of area. A field of one tesla is quite strong: the strongest fields available in laboratories are about 20 teslas, and the Earths magnetic flux density, at its surface, is about 50 microteslas. The tesla, defined in 1958, honors the Serbian-American electrical engineer Nikola Tesla (1856-1943), whose work in electromagnetic induction led to the first practical generators and motors using alternating current. description_zh: “T-M”不是一个已知的物理单位/货币单位，因此无法给出它的常见别名和解释。
没有找到“T-SEC”作为物理单位或货币单位的相关信息。可能是某个特定领域的缩写或简称。
大调羹是体积单位，通常用于烹饪和药物剂量。它等于3个茶匙或约15毫升。在美国和加拿大，一大调羹通常标示为“Tbsp”或“T”，在其他国家可能采用不同的缩写。
description_en: In the US and parts of Canada, a tablespoon is the largest type of spoon used for eating from a bowl. In the UK and most Commonwealth countries, a tablespoon is a type of large spoon usually used for serving. In countries where a tablespoon is a serving spoon, the nearest equivalent to the US tablespoon is either the dessert spoon or the soup spoon. A tablespoonful, nominally the capacity of one tablespoon, is commonly used as a measure of volume in cooking. It is abbreviated as T, tb, tbs, tbsp, tblsp, or tblspn. The capacity of ordinary tablespoons is not regulated by law and is subject to considerable variation. In most countries one level tablespoon is approximately 15?mL; in Australia it is 20?mL.

description_zh: 它是一个纤维线性密度的单位，表示每公克的纤维长度。常用于描述纺织品的质量和强度，特别是纺织品的细度。
description_en: Tex is a unit of measure for the linear mass density of fibers and is defined as the mass in grams per 1000 meters. Tex is more likely to be used in Canada and Continental Europe, while denier remains more common in the United States and United Kingdom. The unit code is tex. The most commonly used unit is actually the decitex, abbreviated dtex, which is the mass in grams per 10,000 meters. When measuring objects that consist of multiple fibers the term filament tex is sometimes used, referring to the mass in grams per 1000 meters of a single filament. Tex is used for measuring fiber size in many products, including cigarette filters, optical cable, yarn, and fabric.
Thailand

keywords_zh: 热力学,热量,热工,热传导

description_zh: 它是热能的单位，用于测量能量的转移和传递，特别是在加热和冷却方面。在美国，它通常写作BTU（British Thermal Unit）。
description_en: (Therm (symbol (thm)) is a non-SI unit of heat energy. It was defined in the United States in 1968 as the energy equivalent of burning 100 cubic feet of natural gas at standard temperature and pressure. In the US gas industry its SI equivalent is defined as exactly (100,000 BTU59^circ F) or (105.4804 megajoules). Public utilities in the U.S. use the therm unit for measuring customer usage of gas and calculating the monthly bills."

description_zh: 石油当量吨是用来比较能量来源的单位，表示产生1吨石油所含有的能量数量，通常用于能源产量和消耗的比较。
description_en: The tonne of oil equivalent (toe) is a unit of energy: the amount of energy released by burning one tonne of crude oil, approximately 42 GJ (as different crude oils have different calorific values, the exact value of the toe is defined by convention; unfortunately there are several slightly different definitions as discussed below). The toe is sometimes used for large amounts of energy, as it can be more intuitive to visualise, say, the energy released by burning 1000 tonnes of oil than 42,000 billion joules (the SI unit of energy). Multiples of the toe are used, in particular the megatoe (Mtoe, one million toe) and the gigatoe (Gtoe, one billion toe).

description_zh: 吨是重量的单位，表示1000公斤或者1千克。常用于测量货物的重量。
吨每天是表示生产率的单位，表示每天生产的物品重量为吨。常用于描述工厂或生产流程的产量。
吨每公顷是一种农业单位，用于表示每公顷的产量或者使用的施肥量。常用于农业和林业领域的数据统计和分析中。
吨每小时是一个用于描述生产或处理速度的单位，表示每小时处理或生产的吨数。常用于工业生产和采矿等领域。

description_en: In the United States, a unit of mass, approximately (29.167, grams). The number of milligrams of precious metal in one assay ton of the ore being tested is equal to the number of troy ounces of pure precious metal in one 2000-pound ton of the ore. i.e. a bead is obtained that weights 3 milligrams, thus the precious metals in the bead would equal three troy ounces to each ton of ore with the understanding that this varies considerably in the real world as the amount of precious values in each ton of ore varies considerably."

description_zh: 它是用于描述制冷系统的冷量的单位，表示一台制冷机每小时制冷能力为1吨（即1000英国热量/小时）。常用于空调、冷库等制冷系统的设计和评估。
description_en: 12000 btu per hour

description_zh: 英吨是英制重量单位制中的一种，等于2240英磅或1016.05公斤。常用于描述船只和货物的重量。长吨是与之相对的缩小版本的单位，等于2000英磅或907.18公斤。
description_en:
""Long ton (weight ton or imperial ton) is the name for the unit called the "ton" in the avoirdupois or Imperial system of measurements, as used in the United Kingdom and several other Commonwealth countries. One long ton is equal to 2,240 pounds (1,016 kg), 1.12 times as much as a short ton, or 35 cubic feet (0.9911 m3) of salt water with a density of 64 lb/ft3 (1.025 g/ml).

It has some limited use in the United States, most commonly in measuring the displacement of ships, and was the unit prescribed for warships by the Washington Naval Treaty 1922-for example battleships were limited to a mass of 35,000 long tons (36,000 t; 39,000 short tons).

""
The long ton per cubic yard density measurement unit is used to measure volume in cubic yards in order to estimate weight or mass in long tons.

description_zh: 公吨是国际制单位制中的质量单位，等于1000千克。它通常用于描述工业和商业中的大宗货物的重量，例如钢材、石油、谷物等。
description_en: The tonne (SI unit symbol: t) is a metric system unit of mass equal to 1,000 kilograms (2,204.6 pounds). It is a non-SI unit accepted for use with SI. To avoid confusion with the ton, it is also known as the metric tonne and metric ton in the United States[3] and occasionally in the United Kingdom. In SI units and prefixes, the tonne is a megagram (Mg), a rarely-used symbol, easily confused with mg, for milligram.

description_zh: ['DerivedUnit', 'Unit']
短吨是美国常用的质量单位，等于2000磅或907.18474千克。它通常用于描述大型物品（如汽车，船舶和机器）的重量。
description_en: The short ton is a unit of mass equal to 2,000 pounds (907.18474 kg). In the United States it is often called simply ton without distinguishing it from the metric ton (tonne, 1,000 kilograms / 2,204.62262 pounds) or the long ton (2,240 pounds / 1,016.0469088 kilograms); rather, the other two are specifically noted. There are, however, some U.S. applications for which unspecified tons normally means long tons.
The short Ton per Hour is a unit used to express a weight processed in a period of time.
The short ton per cubic yard density measurement unit is used to measure volume in cubic yards in order to estimate weight or mass in short tons.

description_zh: 吨是一个计量单位，用于表示质量或重量。但需要注意的是，“Ton”这个单位通常指的是美制吨（short ton），而不是英制吨（long ton）。美制吨的重量是2000磅，约合907公斤，而英制吨的重量是2240磅，约合1016公斤。同时，随着各国采用不同的度量衡体系，对应吨的中文翻译也可能有所不同。
英吨是国际单位制中的质量和重量单位，等于2000磅。它经常被用于美国和其他英语国家。在国际单位制中，吨的单位是公吨。
托是一个压力的单位，等同于在标准重力加速度下，让1毫米汞柱压缩气体所产生的压力。常用于气体压力的测量，尤其是在实验室中。
description_en: The torr is a non-SI unit of pressure with the ratio of 760 to 1 standard atmosphere, chosen to be roughly equal to the fluid pressure exerted by a millimeter of mercury, i.e. , a pressure of 1 torr is approximately equal to one millimeter of mercury. Note that the symbol (Torr) is spelled exactly the same as the unit (torr), but the letter case differs. The unit is written lower-case, while the symbol of the unit (Torr) is capitalized (as upper-case), as is customary in metric units derived from names. Thus, it is correctly written either way, and is only incorrect when specification is first made that the word is being used as a unit, or else a symbol of the unit, and then the incorrect letter case for the specified use is employed.

description_zh: 茶匙是体积单位，表示半流体或粉末状物质的体积大小，通常用于烹饪和烘焙中的配料，它的国际标准是5毫升。
description_en: A teaspoon is a unit of volume. In the United States one teaspoon as a unit of culinary measure is (1/3) tablespoon , that is, (approx 4.93 mL); it is exactly (1/6 U.S. fl. oz), (1/48 ; cup), and (1/768 ; U.S. liquid gallon) (see United States customary units for relative volumes of these other measures) and approximately (1/3 cubic inch). For nutritional labeling on food packages in the U.S., the teaspoon is defined as precisely (5 mL)."
The unit of magnetic induction in the cgs system, (10^{-4},tesla). Also known as the gauss."
Tanzania

description_en: The terabyte is a multiple of the unit byte for digital information. The prefix tera means 10^12 in the International System of Units (SI), and therefore 1 terabyte is 1000000000000bytes, or 1 trillion bytes, or 1000 gigabytes. 1 terabyte in binary prefixes is 0.9095 tebibytes, or 931.32 gibibytes. The unit symbol for the terabyte is TB or TByte, but not Tb (lower case b) which refers to terabit.

description_zh: 太库仑是电荷量的国际单位之一，是指10^12库仑的电荷量。它通常用于描述电子学中极大的电荷量，例如在等离子体物理学和宇宙物理学等领域中。
description_en: A TeraCoulomb is (10^{12} C)."

description_zh: 太赫兹是频率单位，表示每秒钟的振荡次数，常用于描述电磁辐射的波长和频率。太赫兹通常用于研究光谱学、红外线成像和医学诊断。
太焦耳是能量的衡量单位，相当于1兆焦耳（MJ）。常用于描述大规模的能源消耗和生产。
太欧姆是电阻的 SI 单位之一，表示为 10^12欧姆。用于测量电器元件的电阻值。
太瓦是国际制单位制中的功率单位，相当于1兆瓦的10倍，用于表示极大功率，常用于描述能量的产生和传递。
太瓦时是能量单位，表示1兆瓦的功率持续1小时所产生的能量。常用于衡量大型电力系统的能源消耗或发电量。
吨能量是能量单位，表示在一吨燃料燃烧时产生的能量。常用于衡量能源储备和能源消耗。

description_en: The unified atomic mass unit (symbol: (u)) or dalton (symbol: (Da)) is the standard unit that is used for indicating mass on an atomic or molecular scale (atomic mass). It is defined as one twelfth of the mass of an unbound neutral atom of carbon-12 in its nuclear and electronic ground state,[ and has a value of (1.660538921(73) times 10^{-27} kg). One dalton is approximately equal to the mass of one nucleon; an equivalence of saying (1 g mol^{-1}). The CIPM have categorised it as a non-SI unit because units values in SI units must be obtained experimentally."

description_zh: 它是磁矩的单位，表示一个完美的单极子所具有的磁矩大小。相对物理学中，完美的单极子不存在，但该单位仍然在物理学研究中有用途。
description_en: A magnetic pole is a unit pole if it exerts a force of one dyne on another pole of equal strength at a distance of 1 cm. The strength of any given pole in cgs units is therefore numerically equal to the force in dynes which it exerts on a unit pole 1 cm away.

description_zh: 伏特是国际制单位制中的基本单位之一，用于测量电势差或电压。它是以意大利电学家Alessandro Volta（亚历山大·伏尔塔）的名字命名的。
description_en: (Volt is the SI unit of electric potential. Separating electric charges creates potential energy, which can be measured in energy units such as joules. Electric potential is defined as the amount of potential energy present per unit of charge. Electric potential is measured in volts, with one volt representing a potential of one joule per coulomb of charge. The name of the unit honors the Italian scientist Count Alessandro Volta (1745-1827), the inventor of the first battery.  The volt also may be expressed with a variety of other units. For example, a volt is also equal to one watt per ampere (W/A) and one joule per ampere per second (J/A/s).)"

description_zh: 伏安是电学中的一个单位，表示电压和电流的乘积，也就是功率的大小。常用于描述电路中电源的能量传输和负载的能量消耗。
伏特安培小时是电池容量的单位，表示电池能够以多少电功率（伏特安培）工作多长时间（小时）。常用于描述电池的容量和使用寿命。
VAR是一个电力系统中的无功电流单位。它表示电流和电压之间的相位差，用于测量电力系统中的无功功率。无功功率是电力系统中的一种损失能量，但它对设备的运行非常重要。
伏特米是电势差或电压的单位，表示单位电荷在两个点之间所具有的电势差或电压。常用于描述电路中电压的大小。
它是电场强度量纲的单位，用于表示单位长度内电场强度的大小。在电磁学中，也表示静电偏差的程度。
伏特每开尔文（V/K）是一个物理量单位，表示电势或电势差的变化与温度变化的比率。常用于描述温度对电子器件的影响。
伏特每米是电场强度的国际单位，表示单位长度内电场强度的大小。它是衡量电磁场强度的重要参数之一。
description_en: Volt Per Meter (V/m) is a unit in the category of Electric field strength. It is also known as volts per meter, volt/meter, volt/metre, volt per metre, volts per metre. This unit is commonly used in the SI unit system. Volt Per Meter (V/m) has a dimension of (MLT^{-3}I^{-1}) where M is mass, L is length, T is time, and I is electric current. This unit is the standard SI unit in this category."

description_zh: 伏特每平方米是电场强度的单位，表示单位面积内电场强度的大小。常用于描述电磁场的强度。
description_en: The divergence at a particular point in a vector field is (roughly) how much the vector field spreads out from that point. Operationally, we take the partial derivative of each of the field with respect to each of its space variables and add all the derivatives together to get the divergence. Electric field (V/m) differentiated with respect to distance (m) yields (V/(m^2))."

description_zh: 它是电磁学中的一个单位，表示单位时间内电势变化产生的电流。常用于描述电磁场的变化情况。
description_en: Volt per Second is a unit of magnetic flux equaling one weber. This is the flux passing through a conducting loop and reduced to zero at a uniform rate in one second inducing an electric potential of one volt in the loop.

description_zh: 伏特秒每米是电学中的指标，表示电场的强度随时间和空间的变化率，常用于描述电磁场的性质。其国际单位制符号为V·s/m。

label_zh: 平方伏特每平方开尔文

description_zh: 绝对伏特是一个电势单位，表示单位电荷通过电路时所获得的能量。它非常少使用，并且通常只用于学术研究中。
description_en: A unit of electrical potential equal to one hundred millionth of a volt , used in the centimeter-gram-second (CGS) system of units. One abV is the potential difference that exists between two points when the work done to transfer one abcoulomb of charge between them equals: (1,ergcdot,1,abV,=,10,nV)."
In the electromagnetic centimeter-gram-second system of units, abvolt per centimeter is the unit of electric field strength.

The magnetic flux whose expenditure in 1 second produces 1 abvolt per turn of a linked circuit. Technically defined in a three-dimensional system, it corresponds in the four-dimensional electromagnetic sector of the SI system to 10 nWb, and is an impractically small unit. In use for some years, the name was agreed by the International Electrotechnical Committee in 1930, along with a corresponding practical unit, the pramaxwell (or pro-maxwell) = (10^{8}) maxwell."

description_zh: 静电伏特是一个电势差的单位，用于电磁学中描述静电力和电势差。它等于约2.9979伏特。
description_en: "statvolt" is a unit of voltage and electrical potential used in the cgs system of units. The conversion to the SI system is (1 statvolt = 299.792458 volts). The conversion factor 299.792458 is simply the numerical value of the speed of light in m/s divided by 106. The statvolt is also defined in the cgs system as (1 erg / esu). It is a useful unit for electromagnetism because one statvolt per centimetre is equal in magnitude to one gauss. Thus, for example, an electric field of one statvolt/cm has the same energy density as a magnetic field of one gauss. Likewise, a plane wave propagating in a vacuum has perpendicular electric and magnetic fields such that for every gauss of magnetic field intensity there is one statvolt/cm of electric field intensity. The abvolt is another option for a unit of voltage in the cgs system."

""One statvolt per centimetre is equal in magnitude to one gauss. For example, an electric field of one statvolt/cm has the same energy density as a magnetic field of one gauss. Likewise, a plane wave propagating in a vacuum has perpendicular electric and magnetic fields such that for every gauss of magnetic field intensity there is one statvolt/cm of electric field intensity.

The abvolt is another option for a unit of voltage in the cgs system.""

description_zh: 瓦特是一个国际制单位制中的基本单位之一，表示功率。它通常用于描述电力系统中的发电机和负载之间的能量传输。
description_en: The SI unit of power. Power is the rate at which work is done, or (equivalently) the rate at which energy is expended. One watt is equal to a power rate of one joule of work per second of time. This unit is used both in mechanics and in electricity, so it links the mechanical and electrical units to one another. In mechanical terms, one watt equals about 0.001 341 02 horsepower (hp) or 0.737 562 foot-pound per second (lbf/s). In electrical terms, one watt is the power produced by a current of one ampere flowing through an electric potential of one volt. The name of the unit honors James Watt (1736-1819), the British engineer whose improvements to the steam engine are often credited with igniting the Industrial Revolution." ;

description_zh: 瓦时是电能的单位，表示在一小时内功率为1瓦的电器消耗了多少电能。常用于计量家庭和工业用电量。

Watt Per Square Inch is a unit of heat flux or thermal flux, the rate of heat energy transfer through a given surface.

description_en: (Watt per steradian per square metre) is the SI unit of radiance , while that of spectral radiance in frequency is the watt per steradian per square metre per hertz  and that of spectral radiance in wavelength is the watt per steradian per square metre, per metre , commonly the watt per steradian per square metre per nanometre . It has a dimension of (ML^{-4}T^{-3}) where (M) is mass, (L) is length, and (T) is time. This unit is the standard SI unit in this category."

description_zh: 它是用于描述光通量密度的单位，即每单位面积和每球面角度内的辐射功率。常用于光学和光源研究。
description_en: (Watt Per Steradian (W/sr)) is the unit in the category of Radiant intensity. It is also known as watts per steradian. This unit is commonly used in the SI unit system. Watt Per Steradian (W/sr) has a dimension of (Mcdot L^{-2}cdot T^{-3}) where (M) is mass, (L) is length, and (T) is time. This unit is the standard SI unit in this category."

description_zh: 瓦秒是功率和时间的乘积，用于测量能量的大小。它也可以表示焦耳，即单位时间内所传递的能量。常用于描述电能的消耗和生产。
韦伯是国际制单位制中的基本单位之一，用于测量磁通量，代号为“Wb”。它的定义是，当磁通密度为1特斯拉时，通过一个面积为1平方米的平面的磁通量为1韦伯。韦伯通常用于描述电磁场中的磁现象和电动机等的性能。
description_en: The SI unit of magnetic flux. "Flux" is the rate (per unit of time) at which something crosses a surface perpendicular to the flow. The weber is a large unit, equal to (10^{8}) maxwells, and practical fluxes are usually fractions of one weber. The weber is the magnetic flux which, linking a circuit of one turn, would produce in it an electromotive force of 1 volt if it were reduced to zero at a uniform rate in 1 second. In SI base units, the dimensions of the weber are . The weber is commonly expressed in terms of other derived units as the Tesla-square meter , volt-seconds , or joules per ampere ."

description_zh: 韦伯米是电通量密度的国际单位制中的一种，用于度量磁感线的通量密度。它是由韦伯和米的乘积定义而成的。该单位名称在中文中通常被翻译成“韦伯米”。
韦伯每米是一个磁感应强度的单位，表示每米长度内通过的磁通量。常用于描述电磁场和磁性材料的特性。

description_zh: 码是英制单位制中的长度单位之一，相当于3英尺或36英寸，常用于英美国家的测量。在美国，码为美制单位制中最常用的长度单位。
description_en: A yard is a unit of length in several different systems including United States customary units, Imperial units and the former English units. It is equal to 3 feet or 36 inches. Under an agreement in 1959 between Australia, Canada, New Zealand, South Africa, the United Kingdom and the United States, the yard (known as the "international yard" in the United States) was legally defined to be exactly 0.9144 metres.

description_zh: 平方码是英制和美制计量系统中用于测量面积的单位，等于一个正方形边长为1码的面积。常用于房地产和建造行业。
description_en: The square yard is an imperial/US customary unit of area, formerly used in most of the English-speaking world but now generally replaced by the square metre outside of the U.S. , Canada and the U.K. It is defined as the area of a square with sides of one yard in length. (Gaj in Hindi).

description_zh: 立方码是体积的单位，等于一个长、宽、高均为1码的立方体的体积。常用于测量建筑材料的体积，如混凝土、砖块等。
description_en: A cubic yard is an Imperial / U.S. customary unit of volume, used in the United States, Canada, and the UK. It is defined as the volume of a cube with sides of 1 yard in length.

description_zh: 它是一个流量单位，通常用于测量液体或气体的流动速率。表示每天流过一立方码的液体或气体的体积。常用于水力工程、建筑、环境工程等方面。
立方码每小时是用于测量流量的单位，通常用于测量液体或气体等的流量。它表示每小时流过一个立方码的体积。

description_en: "Cubic Yard per Minute" is an Imperial unit for  Volume Per Unit Time expressed as (yd^{3}/min)."

description_zh: 年是时间的单位，它表示地球绕太阳一周的时间，通常用365天、5小时、48分半作为其长度。在农历中，一年通常用12个月来计算。在货币单位中，一年通常被用作计算利息和投资回报率的基础。
description_en: A year is any of the various periods equated with one passage of Earth about the Sun, and hence of roughly 365 days. The familiar calendar has a mixture of 365- and 366-day years, reflecting the fact that the time for one complete passage takes about 365? days; the precise value for this figure depends on the manner of defining the year.

description_zh: Common Year不是一个物理单位/货币单位，而是指一年的长度为365天。这一定义被用于日历中，与闰年的366天相对应。没有中文翻译和常见别名。
恒星年是指地球绕太阳一周，再加上地球相对于恒星的一周，即公转周期为365.25636天的时间。它是天文学中计算行星运动的重要单位。
description_en: A sidereal year is the time taken for Sun to return to the same position with respect to the stars of the celestial sphere.

description_zh: 回归年是指以地球绕太阳公转一周的时间为基础，太阳经过黄道回归点两次之间所经历的时间，一般为365.2421898日。常用于天文学中。
description_en: A tropical year (also known as a solar year), for general purposes, is the length of time that the Sun takes to return to the same position in the cycle of seasons, as seen from Earth; for example, the time from vernal equinox to vernal equinox, or from summer solstice to summer solstice. Because of the precession of the equinoxes, the seasonal cycle does not remain exactly synchronised with the position of the Earth in its orbit around the Sun. As a consequence, the tropical year is about 20 minutes shorter than the time it takes Earth to complete one full orbit around the Sun as measured with respect to the fixed stars. Since antiquity, astronomers have progressively refined the definition of the tropical year, and currently define it as the time required for the mean Suns tropical longitude (longitudinal position along the ecliptic relative to its position at the vernal equinox) to increase by 360 degrees (that is, to complete one full seasonal circuit).

In chemistry and physics, the atomic number (also known as the proton number) is the number of protons found in the nucleus of an atom and therefore identical to the charge number of the nucleus. It is conventionally represented by the symbol Z. The atomic number uniquely identifies a chemical element. In an atom of neutral charge, the atomic number is also equal to the number of electrons.

In physics, the Planck mass, denoted by (m_P), is the unit of mass in the system of natural units known as Planck units. It is defined so that (approx  1.2209 times 10 GeV/c_0 = 2.17651(13) times 10 kg), (or (21.7651 mu g)), where (c_0) is the speed of light in a vacuum, (G) is the gravitational constant, and (hbar) is the reduced Planck constant. Particle physicists and cosmologists often use the reduced Planck mass, which is (approx  4.341 times 10 kg = 2.435  times 10 GeV/c). The added factor of (1/{sqrt{8pi}}) simplifies a number of equations in general relativity. Quantum effects are typified by the magnitude of Plancks constant."
